Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section II, A1 | Description :Monitor and evaluate the progress of the Project and prepare ProjectReports every six months | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section V, 1 | Description :The Recipient shall not later than 18 months after the effective Date,carry out and complete, a joint study with other Project Coun tries, on public private partnerships | Due Date :04-Jun-2012

The Recipient shall conduct no later than twelve months after the Effective Date, an assessment of the proposed new biosafety levelthree in the National Public Health Laboratory, including a risk assessment in line with WHO standards, and an evaluation of themaintenance and operating costs, and share the results with the Association prior to undertaking the respective investments underPart A.1(a) of the Project.

The Recipient shall conduct no later than twelve months after the Effective Date, an assessment of the proposed new biosafety levelthree laboratory, including a risk assessment in line with WHO standards, and an evaluation of the maintenance and operating costs,and share the results with the Association prior to undertaking the respective investments under Part A.1(a) of the Project.

The Recipient shall during the period of implementation of the Project, prepare in form and substance satisfactory to theAssociation, and submit to the Association, six monthly internal audit reports. Each such internal audit shall cover a period ofsix months, and shall be furnished to the Association not later than forty-five days after the end of such period.

The Recipient shall, not later than December 31, 2015: (i) amend the Subsidiary Agreement in form and substance satisfactory to theAssociation; and (ii) furnish to the Association a legal opinion or opinions confirming in form and substance satisfactory to theAssociation that the amended Subsidiary Agreement has been duly authorized or ratified by the Recipient and ECSA and is legallybinding upon the Recipient and ECSA in accordance with its terms.

The Recipient shall, not later than June 30, 2017: (i) amend the Subsidiary Agreement in form and substance satisfactory to theAssociation; and (ii) furnish to the Association a legal opinion or opinions confirming in form and substance satisfactory to theAssociation confirming that the amended Subsidiary Agreement has been duly authorized or ratified by the Recipient and ECSA and islegally binding upon the Recipient and ECSA in accordance with its terms.
